{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "05", "m": "05", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "09", "M": "50", "S": "13"}}, "news": [{"title": "MPCB issues closure notices to 84 RMC units in Pune and Pimpri Chinchwad", "para": "Maharashtra Pollution Control Board has taken strong action against ready mix concrete units in Pune and Pimpri Chinchwad. Many units faced closure notices and directions to fix pollution issues. Stricter norms were introduced, leading to temporary scaling back of inspections. Municipal bodies also intensified their enforcement. The RMC Association protested the actions, seeking better coordination and a single-window clearance system.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/cement/maharashtra-pollution-control-board-cracks-down-on-84-non-compliant-rmc-units/130823134?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-44664/130823134.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "cement"}, {"title": "Telangana government to take over \u20b95,000 crore debt of GHMC", "para": "The Telangana government will assume Rs 5,000 crore in liabilities from the Greater Hyderabad Municipal Corporation (GHMC), significantly easing the debt burden on the civic body. This move aims to strengthen GHMC financially, with the state expected to clear these debts by year-end. The liabilities were primarily incurred for infrastructure projects like flyovers and stormwater drains.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/telangana-government-alleviates-ghmcs-5000-crore-debt-burden/130823172?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-39890/130823172.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Hyderabad leads South India\u2019s luxury housing market with \u20b98,562 crore sales in FY26: Report", "para": "Hyderabad accounted for the highest value of ultra-luxury housing sales in South India during FY26, while Bengaluru recorded the sharpest growth in demand. Chennai remained a smaller, niche market.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/hyderabad-dominates-south-indias-ultra-luxury-housing-market-with-8562-crore-sales-in-fy26/130824726?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-225992/130824726.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}]}